                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2052</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1915-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1915-12-06T00:00:00+00:00">undated</date> [<hi rend="italic"
                            >Received December 9, 1915</hi>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>With a view to meeting American complaints <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward
                        Grey</persName> is ready to set up a small unofficial committee of persons
                    of experience who shall examine any specific case in which an allegation is made
                    of unnecessary delay in dealing with ships and cargoes from the United States.
                    This committee would also suggest any improvements in the machinery for the
                    purpose of preventing such delays in other cases.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
